1) 
The sentences on the right follow those on the left.
Which sentence goes with which?
Please don´t make Much noise.
It's been late.
I need to eat something soon.
I´m getting hungry.
I don´t have anywhere to live right now.
I´m looking for an apartment.
We need to leave soon.
It´s starting to rain.
They don´t need their car any more.
They´re trying to sell it.
Things are not so good at work.
The company is losing money.
It isn´t true what they said.
They´re lying.

 
2.

Complete the conversations:

I saw Brian a few days ago.

Oh, did you?

What´s he doing these days?

He´s at university.

What is he studying?

Psychology.

Is he enjoying it?

Yeas, he says it´s a very good course.

Hi, Nicola.

How is going your new job?

Not bad.

It wasn´t so good at first, but it´s geting better now.

What about Daniel?

Is he OK?

Yes, but he are not enjoying his work right now.

He´s been in the same job for a long time and he is beginning to get bored with it

 
